<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 5:48PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Oldham
and northwestern Deaf Smith Counties through 615 PM CDT...
At 548 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles south of Glenrio, or 35 miles northwest of Friona, moving
northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Adrian and Glenrio.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
